{
  "stem": "27507.4",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I used later on in 1941 and in 1942 when I sometimes went and wanted to have a quiet hour, I would go with a book and sit in the garden there and read.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And whoever heard-- and there-- there existed-- there existed a serum against typhoid, which according to what I was told was a serum invented by Dr.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Weigl in Lwow in Poland.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But that serum was absolutely rare and very difficult to get and terribly expensive.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But of course whoever managed to have the money together, then they would-- they would get immunized.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I think my parents were immunized, but I think I was not immunized.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I think the serum was not considered safe for children.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I was not immunized, but I-- but there was this constant fear in those times that one would get infected.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And my mother was-- who was absolutely crazy about hygiene, would always tell when I came home in those days, she would tell me to undress at the entrance and check all my clothes that one didn't find any lice because lice were the carriers of the-- of the typhoid.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And somehow, she-- we-- we managed to stay OK.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Somehow we managed to avoid the disease.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But that winter in '40, '41, many, many people died from typhoid.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That was the-- that's [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "How to say?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I don't know.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It's not a-- it's not a typhoid, an intestinal typhoid, but it's a typhoid causing spots.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Anyway, and-- Did they have any hospital or doctors, nurses, anything?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, but were-- there were doctors and nurses, yes.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And We were lucky, again, that one of my-- an-- an uncle, husband of my youngest aunt was a doctor, was a surgeon.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
